In article <p47QWh4.leeedwards@delphi.com>,  <leeedwards@delphi.com> wrote:
>Does anyone know where to get a program for the PC which operates as
>a virtual German Enigma machine?

I think there is one on the Applied Cryptography source disks.
But an Enigma simulation would hardly count as good encryption software.
Enigma encryption was broken by the Poles and English over 50 years
ago without even using computers.  Try PGP instead.
